      "unidentified": "",
      "value": "<p>&gt;<span>@UUID[Compendium.sfrpg.class-features.g2Q23s8Vz7qnck3F]{Arcane}</span></p>\n<p>As a reaction whenever you cast a spell that has no effect (such as the affected creatures all succeeding at saving throws or being immune), you can spend a number of Resolve Points equal to half the spell’s level (rounded up) to capture the spell’s magical energy and retain it as a spell echo for a number of rounds equal to your Wisdom modifier (minimum 1). Once during this time, you can cast the captured spell a second time by expending the spell echo instead of expending a spell slot. You can have only one spell echo at a time.</p>"
